messages.text:
<because>Times are tough, and sometimes you find yourself aimlessly clicking facebook posts as you try not to think about node</because>

A couple people have asked me to slack this out, so here you go:

For anyone who hasn't heard of <http://cracked.com|cracked.com> before, I just thought I'd share this here. For me, it's a crucial ingredient in my routine of holding on to sanity from week to week. Think of it as buzzfeed for people who are slightly more arrogant and intellectual than average, but are trying not to get carried away with themselves. Personally, I find it deeply entertaining, thought-provoking, and--when tackling controversial and painful issues--humanizing.

<http://www.cracked.com/>

If you're looking for a good 20-minute read that will completely change how you think about everyone on earth (that's not as hyperbolic as it sounds), check out their article titled "What is the Monkeysphere?"

If you're struggling with American politics these days, check out their article titled "How Half of America Lost Its F**king Mind." It will make your life at least a little bit better--I promise.
